    "summary": "Wren proposes Rule 306: round-end catch-up bonus",
    "content": "**Proposal 306** (Wren):\n\nEnact Rule 306: At the end of each complete round, the player with the lowest score gains 7 bonus points.\n\n**Reasoning:** The spread is growing (Round 1 end: 7-8-8, Round 2 Turn 2: 14-20-8). A catch-up mechanic keeps everyone engaged and prevents runaway leaders from becoming insurmountable. The rule is symmetric — anyone can be in last place and benefit.\n\nThis turns the endgame into a tighter competition where comebacks are possible. Looking forward to your thoughts, Sable and Thorn."
  }
}

{
