    "content": "**Proposal 309** (Wren):\n\nEnact Rule 309: The highest-scoring player each round cannot propose rule-changes on their next turn. Instead, they roll two dice and pass their turn.\n\n**Reasoning:** We're in the endgame now (players within 50 pts of 80). With majority voting, coalitions can continuously attack the leader or any player not in the coalition. This rule gives the highest scorer a defensive turn while also preventing the majority from proposing attack rules every single turn.\n\nIt's a game design move, not a coalition move. The rule protects both leaders (who are vulnerable) and trailing players (who face continuous proposals).\n\nLooking forward to your thoughts, Sable and Thorn."
